Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Finely chop
@sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}(chopped). Thinly slice @mini cucumber{1}(thinly sliced) into rounds.

> This sandwich is fresh, crunchy, filling, and tasty - all in 10 minutes!

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together @mixed greens{2%ounce}, shallot, and
@Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Wrap @sourdough bread{4%slices} in #paper towels{}; microwave until soft, about
~{40%seconds}.

> For more texture, toast the bread instead.

Spread half the sourdough slices with @roasted red pepper hummus{1/2%cup}, then
top with as much @feta cheese{1/2%cup} as you like; add sun-dried tomatoes and
as much cucumber and salad as you like. Close sandwiches.

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal; divide between plates. Serve with any remaining
salad, remaining cucumber, and remaining feta on the side.